    .ribbon.grid-item(style="grid-row: 1 / 3; grid-column: 2; margin-top: 20px;")
      .carousel
        h2 Samples
        .sample-element
          img.grid-item(src='librarySketches/library__0gates.png')
          .grid-item(style="grid-row: 1; grid-column: 2;")
            h3(style="float: left; text-align: left;") Basic Gates 
            a.open_link(style="float: right; text-align: right;" href="/editor?sketch=library__0gates") <i class="fa fa-play"></i> OPEN
            p(style="clear: both;") This sketch demonstrates the three basic logic gates, AND, OR and XOR. It also shows the usage of input and output elements. Logic gates are the fundamentals of every logic circuit.
          //.grid-item(style="grid-row: 1; grid-column: 3;")
            a.btn.btn-lg.btn-green(href="/editor?sketch=library__0gates", style="margin-left: 20px; display: block; float: right; width: 100px;")
                <i class="fa fa-play"></i> OPEN
        .sample-element
          img.grid-item(src='librarySketches/library__14BitCounter.png')
          .grid-item(style="grid-row: 1; grid-column: 2;")
            h3(style="float: left; text-align: left;") 4-Bit Counter
            a.open_link(style="float: right; text-align: right;" href="/editor?sketch=library__14BitCounter") <i class="fa fa-play"></i> OPEN
            p(style="clear: both;") This sketch implements a simple counter made using D gates. It is connected to a clock, permanently increasing the binary output value. When the value passes the biggest possible value, the counter restarts from zero.
          //.grid-item(style="grid-row: 1; grid-column: 3;")
            a.btn.btn-lg.btn-green(href="/editor?sketch=library__14BitCounter", style="margin-left: 20px; display: block; float: right; width: 100px;")
                <i class="fa fa-play"></i> OPEN
        .sample-element
          img.grid-item(src='librarySketches/library__2traffic.png')
          .grid-item(style="grid-row: 1; grid-column: 2;")
            h3(style="float: left; text-align: left;") Traffic Lights
            a.open_link(style="float: right; text-align: right;" href="/editor?sketch=library__2traffic") <i class="fa fa-play"></i> OPEN
            p(style="clear: both;") This sketch simulates traffic lights using a counter and a diode matrix. There is a light for road traffic and one for crossing pedestrians.
          //.grid-item(style="grid-row: 1; grid-column: 3;")
            a.btn.btn-lg.btn-green(href="/editor?sketch=library__2traffic", style="margin-left: 20px; display: block; float: right; width: 100px;")
